content:
To add the ability to archive a case, you could create a new property in the `Case` model, such as `archived` which could be a Boolean indicating whether the case has been archived or not. You could then add a new endpoint to the `case_management` module to allow users to archive or unarchive cases. The API could look something like this:
```bash
POST /cases/:id/archive
Request body:
{
    "archived": true
}

Response body:
{
    "message": "Case archived successfully"
}
```
And to unarchive a case:
```bash
POST /cases/:id/archive
Request body:
{
    "archived": false
}

Response body:
{
    "message": "Case unarchived successfully"
}
```
You could also consider adding a new endpoint to retrieve all archived cases:
```bash
GET /cases/archived

Response body:
{
    "cases": [
        {
            "id": 1,
            "patient_name": "John Doe",
            "implant_system": "ACME Spinal Implant System",
            "archived": true,
            ...
        },
        {
            "id": 2,
            "patient_name": "Jane Smith",
            "implant_system": "XYZ Spinal Implant System",
            "archived": true,
            ...
        }
    ]
}
```
This would allow users to view and manage their archived cases separately from their active cases.
